Me examining myself in laning phase:

&quot;Wait... why did I go for that trade? The jungler is probably top side. I&#039;ll just do a really short trade -dies- IF ONLY I HAD A JU-- no.. .wait. I knew he was here. Why did I fight that? Wave is too big. I shouldnt try to trade and just farm until it drops a little bit. -Tries to trade, gets chunked- FUCKING JUN-- no, wait... I already said I should be careful. I blew both summs and ulti is down. I shouldnt fight or play aggro until I see the enemy jgler somewhere else on the map. -trades and gets ganked- FUCK- - why do I even bother. It&#039;s my fault. What the--&quot;

In the back of my mind:

&quot;Plat elo players fight too much&quot;
&quot;Plat players fight too much&quot;
&quot;Plat, fight&quot;
&quot;STOP FIGHTING EVERY SINGLE SECOND&quot;

Those words resonated with me.
